    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - BAROMETRIC
        PRESSURE (BARO) SENSOR - TESTING APS/IVS CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING APS/IVS CIRCUITS</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If fault codes indicate a problem is also present with the APS/IVS system, troubleshoot that
                    system before performing the following test.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If BARO flash code 151 or 152 is active, perform Testing Barometric Pressure Sensor Circuits
                (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_143.xml" xrefid="ef1251810">3.17</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <para>This test systematically checks the BARO circuits for:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Short circuits to ground.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Short circuits to unwanted voltage sources.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Open circuits or excessive circuit resistance.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Proper feeds and grounds.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
